  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Post-Warranty Thermador Range Specialists</h2>
      <p>Thermador backs the Professional line with a two-year parts-and-labor warranty and a five-year sealed-system term. Once those run out, the factory network hands you off — and that's where we come in. Our techs have serviced every Pro Grand, Pro Harmony, and Professional Series range built since 2010, from the 30-inch PRG304WH on up to the 60-inch PRD606JDSGU with dual ovens and a Pro Indoor Grill. We see the same failure patterns again and again, and we stock the parts that match.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>What We See on Thermador Ranges Across LA</h2>
      <p>Our dispatch board in Van Nuys sees Thermador range calls every single day of the week. From the Pro Harmony 36-inch ranges in condos off Wilshire to the Pro Grand 48-inch dual-fuel rigs in Malibu Colony and Beverly Park, the patterns cluster tighter than most brands. The Star Burner ignition has a year 6-to-8 window where the spark electrode drifts out of tolerance. The ExtraLow simmer valve starts cycling off around the same time — LA hard water and gas regulator aging both contribute. Convection fan motors on the 22,000 BTU power-burner side wear faster than the standard side because they run at higher duty cycle. None of this is Thermador building a bad range — it's what happens when a serious pro-style range lives through 3,000 meals a year.</p>
      <p>We don't swap parts without understanding why they failed. A Star Burner igniter that's arced through in year 4 is a symptom, not the disease — usually it's a valve seat that's letting a touch of gas weep while the burner's off, corroding the electrode tip. We replace both. That's the part that keeps your next repair off the calendar.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Thermador Range Models We Service</h2>
      <h3>Pro Grand Series — 48" &amp; 60" Dual-Fuel Flagships</h3>
      <p>The Pro Grand line is the flagship — dual fuel, six sealed Star Burners, the 5.1 cu ft primary convection oven, the 1.4 cu ft steam oven, the integrated electric griddle, and the Pro Indoor Grill on select configurations. These are the ranges you'll find in new-build Bel Air and Beverly Park kitchens alongside a Sub-Zero column and a Wolf cooktop. We service every Pro Grand built: <strong>PRD48JDSGU, PRD48NLSGU, PRD486GDHU, PRD486JDGU, PRD606JDSGU, PRD606WIG</strong>, and the 2022+ Home Connect revisions.</p>

      <h3>Pro Harmony Series — 30", 36" &amp; 48" All-Gas Pro-Style</h3>
      <p>Pro Harmony is the all-gas pro-style range that anchors mid-tier builds across West Hollywood and Sherman Oaks. Same Star Burner, same ExtraLow, same 22,000 BTU power burner as the Pro Grand — just a larger single oven instead of the dual cavity. Common service across: <strong>PRG304WH, PRG364GDH, PRG366WG, PRG486GDH, PRG486JDG, PRG486WDH</strong>.</p>

      <h3>Professional Series — Dual Fuel 30" &amp; 36"</h3>
      <p>The Professional Series is the dual-fuel 30 and 36-inch range that lives in most renovated kitchens in Hancock Park, Studio City, and the 90077 side of Bel Air. Electric convection oven, gas cooktop, Star Burners. We stock parts for: <strong>PRD304WHU, PRD364GDHU, PRD366WIG, PRD366WIGU</strong>.</p>

      <h3>Masterpiece Series — Induction &amp; Electric Ranges</h3>
      <p>The Masterpiece line covers induction ranges and slide-in electric ranges — newer product, so fewer post-warranty calls, but when they come in it's usually an IGBT fault showing F63 or an induction coil sensing failure on the front left zone. Models we service: <strong>MES301WS, MES301YS, induction slide-ins 30" and 36"</strong>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Star Burner &amp; ExtraLow — What Makes Thermador Ranges Worth Fixing</h2>
      <p>Thermador's patent on the five-point pedestal Star Burner isn't marketing filler — it genuinely matters for how we diagnose ignition problems. The burner head has 56% more flame-port perimeter than a round burner of the same size, which spreads heat under a 12-inch pan with no cold spot. But it also means the spark electrode has to land within tight tolerances against the star tip — shift it even a millimeter and you get the clicking-but-no-ignition symptom that drives the after-hours calls.</p>
      <p>ExtraLow is the other signature system. It's a secondary low-BTU gas valve that activates below the main valve's minimum, holding flame as low as 100°F for a real hollandaise. When ExtraLow sticks or calibrates out — usually 6 to 9 years in — the burner cycles off under sustained low heat, or the flame jumps back to full when you back off the knob. Both failures trace to the same valve assembly; we replace it from underneath with the cooktop tilted.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Common Thermador Range Problems We Fix</h2>

      <h3>Star Burner won't ignite — continuous clicking</h3>
      <p>Nine times out of ten, either the spark electrode has shifted from the star-tip geometry (we re-index or replace), or a boil-over flooded the igniter well (we pull the burner base, dry the ceramic, test continuity). If the spark module itself has failed, we replace it from under the cooktop.</p>

      <h3>ExtraLow simmer cycles off mid-cook</h3>
      <p>Secondary low-BTU valve sticking or out of calibration. Valve assembly replacement. Same visit.</p>

      <h3>Convection fan noise or fan not turning</h3>
      <p>22,000 BTU power-burner side convection fan motor tends to wear first. We carry OEM motors for Pro Grand and Pro Harmony. On Pro Grand dual-fuel the upper oven fan is separately wired from the lower — we diagnose each independently.</p>

      <h3>Oven not heating — F1, F3, F34 error codes</h3>
      <p>F3/F34 is the RTD (oven temperature sensor) — fast replacement from the rear. F1 is control board communication — we test the harness before condemning the board. If the bake element itself has failed open (no display error, just no heat), that's a 45-minute rear-access swap.</p>

      <h3>Self-clean won't engage or door won't lock</h3>
      <p>Door-lock motor or latch assembly. On Pro Grand the lock is under the cooktop rear lip — takes the rear trim off but it's a clean job.</p>

      <h3>Steam oven (1.4 cu ft) not generating steam</h3>
      <p>Pro Grand dual-fuel's steam oven runs off a separate water line and steam generator. Usually either the water solenoid is clogged with mineral scale (LA water), or the generator heating element has failed. We diagnose the water side first — it's cheaper.</p>

      <h3>Griddle not heating evenly — 6-pass 1630W element</h3>
      <p>The 6-pass griddle element fails in segments, which shows as cold spots when you're cooking pancakes. Full element replacement.</p>

      <h3>Warming drawer not heating</h3>
      <p>Thermistor or element. 20-minute diagnosis, 45-minute repair.</p>

      <h3>Gas-to-LP conversion (or reverse)</h3>
      <p>Our techs carry factory Thermador conversion kits for every current Pro Grand and Pro Harmony configuration. Tell dispatch before scheduling. About 90 minutes on a 48-inch, 60 on a 36-inch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Non-Invasive Service for Built-In &amp; Cabinet-Flush Installs</h2>
      <p>Most Thermador Pro Grand installs sit flush with $8,000 to $30,000 worth of custom cabinetry on both sides. When we pull a range for rear-access work — RTD sensor, convection fan, oven bake element — we photograph the install first, use suction-cup grips and cabinet skates, and re-level on the way back in. No scuffed millwork, no warranty-voiding disassembly. It's how we work on every built-in we touch, from Sub-Zero columns to Miele coffee systems.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Factory Service vs Independent — Where We Fit</h2>
      <p>BSH (Thermador's parent) runs an authorized factory network for in-warranty claims, and it's the right call if your range is still inside the two-year parts-and-labor window. We tell clients that straight. Where we come in is the 70% of calls where the warranty's expired, the factory-authorized techs are booked three weeks out, or the client's had a bad handoff and wants someone who'll actually show up. Our techs have the same training tree — BSH's T-Series modules on open-burner calibration, dual-fuel diagnostics, and Home Connect resets — and we're non-authorized, which means our labor rates aren't set by a warranty reimbursement schedule. That usually saves 15-25% on post-warranty work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>How the Repair Actually Runs</h2>

      <h3>1. Call or text a photo</h3>
      <p>Fastest path. Snap the error code screen or the burner that won't light, text it to your nearest branch. We'll tell you probable cause and an AOV range before we dispatch. <strong><a href={`tel:${mainPhone.tel}`}>{mainPhone.phone}</a></strong> is LA main; branch numbers below.</p>

      <h3>2. Two-hour window, same day when possible</h3>
      <p>Calls placed before 11 a.m. almost always get a same-day window. Emergency dispatches (freezer-adjacent range, gas leak smell) run until 9 p.m.</p>

      <h3>3. $89 diagnostic — waived with repair</h3>
      <p>Flat. We test, we diagnose, we write a written estimate. If you approve the repair, the $89 goes away. If you don't, you pay the $89 and owe nothing else.</p>

      <h3>4. OEM parts, two-year Thermador warranty preserved</h3>
      <p>We use genuine Thermador parts — matters for your insurance and for preserving any remaining sealed-system warranty on newer ranges. 90-day labor guarantee on our work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Recent Thermador Range Repairs</h2>

      <h3>Beverly Hills 90210 — PRD48JDSGU Star Burner cluster ignition failure</h3>
      <p>Six-burner Pro Grand 48 dual-fuel, three front burners clicking but not lighting. Diagnosis: spark module had failed, throwing partial spark to front rail only. Our techs pulled the cooktop, swapped the module and the two most-corroded electrodes, re-indexed all six. Total time on site: 2 hours 10 minutes.</p>

      <h3>Malibu Colony — PRG486GDH ExtraLow valve cycling</h3>
      <p>Nine-year-old Pro Harmony 48 all-gas. Owner reported ExtraLow dropping out on sustained low-heat sauces. Secondary valve assembly replacement from underneath, calibration at 100°F verified with pyrometer. Back to holding a 4-hour braise.</p>

      <h3>Sherman Oaks — PRD364GDHU F34 error code, oven dead</h3>
      <p>Professional Series 36 dual-fuel, seven years old. F34 on display, no heat. RTD sensor out of spec — replaced from the rear, calibrated the oven at 350°F, 400°F, 450°F. 55 minutes on site.</p>

      <h3>Pasadena Oak Knoll — PRD606JDSGU steam oven generator</h3>
      <p>Pro Grand 60-inch dual-fuel with steam. Steam oven wasn't generating. Water solenoid had scaled shut from LA hard water. Cleaned the solenoid, flushed the feed line, ran a full steam cycle. We recommended an in-line water filter for the dedicated steam feed going forward.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Districts We Cover for Thermador</h2>
      <p>Beverly Hills · Bel Air · Holmby Hills · Malibu (Colony, Carbon Beach, Point Dume) · Pacific Palisades (Riviera, Huntington Palisades) · Brentwood (Mandeville Canyon, Crestwood Hills) · Hollywood Hills (Bird Streets, Outpost Estates) · West Hollywood (Norma Triangle, Sunset Strip) · Beverly Grove · Hancock Park · Larchmont · Sherman Oaks (South of Ventura) · Studio City · Encino · Hidden Hills · Calabasas · Pasadena (Oak Knoll, Hastings Ranch) · San Marino · La Cañada Flintridge · Thousand Oaks (Sherwood Country Club) · Westlake Village · Manhattan Beach · Palos Verdes Estates · Rancho Palos Verdes · Newport Beach · Corona del Mar · Laguna Beach</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Why People Call Us for Thermador Range Repair</h2>
      <ul class="why-list">
        <li><strong>Every tech on staff has worked Pro Grand, Pro Harmony, and Professional Series ranges.</strong> We don't cross-train a washer guy onto a $15,000 pro range and hope.</li>
        <li><strong>OEM parts only.</strong> Counterfeit Star Burner igniters will work for 6 weeks and then arc out — we've seen the damage, we don't touch them.</li>
        <li><strong>Direct pricing.</strong> $89 diagnostic, waived with repair. Written estimate before we lift a screwdriver. No line-item padding.</li>
        <li><strong>5 LA-area branches.</strong> West Hollywood, LA Main, Thousand Oaks, Pasadena, Irvine — dispatch by neighborhood, not by who answers first.</li>
        <li><strong>Text-a-photo workflow.</strong> Approved by Twilio A2P 10DLC. Snap it, send it, we'll reply with a probable cause and ballpark before we roll a truck.</li>
        <li><strong>Non-invasive built-in protocol.</strong> We photograph the install, use cabinet skates and suction grips, re-level on reinstall. No scuffs.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gray">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What Thermador Range Owners Say</h2>
      <p class="review-placeholder"><em>Reviews loaded from GMB — aggregate rating 4.6 across 37 reviews. Pull real Thermador-specific reviews from West Hollywood, LA, and Thousand Oaks GMB profiles before go-live.</em></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Thermador Range Repair Pricing in LA</h2>
      <p>We publish our ranges up front. Every quote is flat-rate after the $89 diagnostic — no surprises on the invoice.</p>

      <table class="pricing-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical Range</th></tr>
        </thead>
